<br>
So, I go for the root and shoot.  This zone is perfect for the snare use, due to the lack of wandering aggros, but in some zones like Oasis and such .. the snare trick almost always ended up with me having 10 things on my tail.  So, I am learning that different places call for different tactics.  <br>
<br>
Were I playing a Druid, I would snare my life away.  But as a Ranger , especially one building bow skill, root and shoot is a blast.  Important note here is that I rarely root, only do it to put distance between me and foe, when it is kicking my butt.  I root it, back off, then snare, flame lick and proceed.  Works well.  And it allows me to get in non-interrupted spells, thereby allow me to go full bore on the attack when it closes.  The times where I was not the main tank was alot different.  I would basically flame lick and then snare as it got down in health so we wouldn't have to chase it into other aggros.<br>
<br>
My guess is, the tactics will change once again as I mett different opponents, but I am becoming quite well known in the zone as a heck of a good ranger, that knows how to use all my weapons, and is willing to die to protect others.  Thats a good rep to have as it is becoming easy to find groups.  <br>
